article.headline: Siena 98, Niagara 92 (2OT)
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Kenny Hasbrouck made five 3-pointers and finished with 25 points to lead Siena to a 98-92 victory over Niagara in double overtime on Saturday night. After Niagara's Clif Brown missed a 3-pointer that would have tied the game with 18 seconds left, Tay Fisher was fouled as he grabbed the rebound for Siena (15-12, 10-8). He sank one of his two free throws to make it a two-possession game. Antoine Jordan, who finished with 19 points for the Saints, sealed the win on two free throws with three seconds remaining. In regulation, Hasbrouck tied the game on a 3-pointer with 44 seconds to play. Niagara got the ball, but Brown missed a running layup. Kojo Mensah scored 21 points and dished out 12 assists for Siena, while Mike Beers had five 3-pointers on his way to 18 points. Lorenzo Miles led the Purple Eagles (10-17, 7-11) with 26 points, including six 3-pointers. James Mathis had 21 points and 15 rebounds, while Brown finished with 19 points and 13 rebounds. J.R. Duffey contributed 16 points. Although Niagara outrebounded Siena 51-27, the Saints shot 55 percent from the floor and 48 percent from 3-point range. The win guarantees the Saints will finish with a winning record, a year after they had a school-high 24 losses.
